s (NMS) recently collaborated with KURA for the construction of a 28-kilometer road in Kibra as part of its project to rehabilitate 444 kilometers of roads expected to be completed in one year’s time. eval(ez_write_tag([[250,250],'constructionreviewonline_com-banner-1','ezslot_1',612,'0','0']));According to the NMS Boss, Mohammed Badi, the aim of the 444-kilometer road project is to increase accessibility in the informal settlements. The areas that will benefit from this project include Kawangware, Riruta, parts of Dagoretti North, Mathare, Kangemi, and Mukuru,  as well as Kibera, parts of Githurai 44 and 45, Mwiki, and Zimmermann.